msgstr ""

#: ../../04_venue_selection.md:6
msgid "Accessibility Considerations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../04_venue_selection.md:7
msgid "Consider attendees who may need accommodations for a disability"
msgstr ""

#: ../../04_venue_selection.md:9
msgid "Mobility"
msgstr ""

#: ../../04_venue_selection.md:11
msgid ""
"üçé Reserve seats in rooms for folks who might need it (wheelchair, crutches, "
"cane, etc.). Choose easily-accessible seats, such as at the end of a row on "
"the aisle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../04_venue_selection.md:12
msgid ""
"üçé Create wide aisles (2.5m so two power chairs can pass each other) between "
"chairs to make it easier for people who are mobility-impaired to navigate "
"the room."
msgstr ""

#: ../../04_venue_selection.md:13
msgid ""
"Reduce conference sprawl to support access for people who are mobility-"
"impaired."
msgstr ""

#: ../../04_venue_selection.md:14
msgid ""
"Consider marking and enforcing \"No Standing Zones\" through rooms such as "
"foyers that are both gathering areas and regions people must pass through. "
"(A 2.5m \"corridor\" marked on the ground in yellow tape is ideal.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../04_venue_selection.md:15
msgid ""
"Consider making remote access available via livestream, recorded talks, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../04_venue_selection.md:16
msgid ""
"Make sure the building is wheelchair accessible. (In U.S. this is typically "
"required by law.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../04_venue_selection.md:17
msgid ""
"Be aware of how far/near the closest wheelchair-accessible restrooms are. "
"Attempt to shorten this distance when possible and be sure all staff know "
"where to direct attendees who require a wheelchair-accessible restroom."
msgstr ""

#: ../../04_venue_selection.md:19
msgid "Create Access Visual & Hearing Disabilities"
msgstr ""

#: ../../04_venue_selection.md:21
msgid ""
"‚úÖ Book sign-language interpreters and/or real-time captioning (someone "
"typing captions) for deaf and hard-of-hearing attendees."
msgstr ""

#: ../../04_venue_selection.md:22
msgid ""
"If budget does not allow for both sign-language interpreters and captioning,"
" we suggest that you opt for captioning as it tends to create more access "
"for a greater number of people. (See \"Further Reading\" below.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../04_venue_selection.md:23
msgid ""
"Select a venue that has a hearing loop, or audio induction loop (a special "
"type of sound system for use by people with hearing aids) and make sure it "
"is used"
msgstr ""

#: ../../04_venue_selection.md:25
msgid "Signage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../04_venue_selection.md:26
msgid ""
"Consider using patterns rather than just color on signs and presentation "
"slides to indicate differences, to make comprehension easier for attendees "
"with color blindness/low vision issues."
msgstr ""

#: ../../04_venue_selection.md:27
msgid "Provide large-text signs and easy-to-read maps."
msgstr ""

#: ../../04_venue_selection.md:28
msgid "Send maps to attendees in advance, with the event schedule."
msgstr ""

#: ../../04_venue_selection.md:29
msgid ""
"Provide large-print copies of printed materials, such as program booklets, "
"via printing normally A5 documents on A4, or folded A4-booklets on A3."
msgstr ""

#: ../../04_venue_selection.md:31
msgid "Microphones"
msgstr ""

#: ../../04_venue_selection.md:32
msgid ""
"üçé Ask conference organizers to announce important information over the "
"microphone, which helps people with impaired vision."
msgstr ""

#: ../../04_venue_selection.md:33
msgid "Make sure that hand-held microphones are available"
msgstr ""

#: ../../04_venue_selection.md:34
msgid ""
"Encourage session chairs to repeat questions from the audience over the mic "
"so everyone can hear"
msgstr ""

#: ../../04_venue_selection.md:35
msgid ""
"Session chairs should ensure that the microphone is used (even if the "
"speaker thinks their voice is loud enough)"
msgstr ""

